<h3><a name=theses>Ph.D. Theses Directed</a></h3>
<ol>
<li>David A. Odell, Trace Constructions in alpha-Recursion Theory (1983).
<li>Christine A. Haught, Turing and Truth-table Degrees of 1-Generic and
Recursively Enumerable Sets (1985). (Now Associate Professor, Loyola
University, Chicago, IL.)
<li>Mark F. Simpson, Arithmetic Degrees: Initial Segments, omega-<i>REA</i>
Operators and the omega-jump (1985). (Now Manager, Imaging
Architectures, Apple Computer, Santa Clara, CA.)
<li>Steven Kautz, Degrees of Random Sets (1991). (Now Associate Professor,
Randolph Macon College for Women, Lynchburg, VA.)
<li>Yue Yang, Priority Arguments and Reverse Mathematics (1992). (Now
Assistant Professor, National University of Singapore.)
<li>David Reed Solomon, <a href="theses/reed.ps">The Reverse Mathematics of 
Ordered Groups</a> (1998) (<a href="theses/reed.dvi">.dvi version</a>).(Now
NSF Postdoctoral Fellow and Assistant Professor, University of Wisconsin, Madison.)
<li>Denis Hirschfeldt, <a href="theses/denis.ps">Degree Spectra of Relations 
on Computable Structures</a> (1999) (<a href="theses/denis.dvi">.dvi version</a>).
(L. E. Dickson Instructor, University of Chicago.)
<li><a href="http://www.udallas.edu/mathdept/faculty/wmwhite/">
Walker White</a>, <a href="theses/Walker.ps">Characterizations for 
Computable Structures</a> (2000) (<a href="theses/Walker.dvi">.dvi version</a>).
(Now Assistant Professor, University of Dallas.)
</ol>

